		   <table class="mform2"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform2" valign="top" id="forumSubject">
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Fri, Mar 5th 1:54 PM2004 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class="sm">IP: Logged</span> | <a class="sm" href="/db/classes.html?class=8&mid=107845432730450&num=6&post=1&replyto=1078512785397877516"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." height="11" width="17" /> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=1078512785397877516></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=295850"><span id=>Jaked</span></a><b><span id=></span></b><br />12 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Jaked&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;     Quading is a pretty simple thing to do, however you can't do it effectively until lvl 34. At 34 you get lightning strike which is a 170 some pt. area effect spell (direct dmg).  <br>       The way to do it is grab 4 mobs, snare them all, get them in a tight bunch, and run... cast... run...cast...etc. til they are all dead. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </p><br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br />Bvardar 24 Bard<br>Fonadarn 16 Necromancer<br>Dabigger 3 Warrior<br>Seeas 50 Druid <br>Torvonillius<br>&lt; a href="<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=915233"&gt;Inspect" target="akztarg">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=915233"&gt;Inspect</a> Me&lt; /a&gt;</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8"></td><td align="right" id="fs8" >0 Replies</td></tr></table>
</td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td>

		   <table class="mform"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top" id="forumSubject">
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Wed, May 19th 4:20 AM2004 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class="sm">IP: Logged</span> | <a class="sm" href="/db/classes.html?class=8&mid=107845432730450&num=6&post=1&replyto=1084954777761038298"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." height="11" width="17" /> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=1084954777761038298></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=176850"><span id=Scholar>vorro</span></a><b><span id=Scholar><br>Scholar</span></b><br />23 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=vorro&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>The best place for you to start learning how to quad is in oasis of marr. Get up wolf form and levitate, and make sure you have lightning strike and ensnare loaded, as well as a good heal, just in case.<br><br>Get in range, and snare one of the spectres on spectre isle. There's a good change you'll get some adds here. Don't worry. Adds are the name of the game when you're quadding. Luckily for you, they are much slower than you, esp. when you're sowed and they're snared.<br><br>Get all the adds snared. Now, once you get them all snared, start running around them in a circular pattern. They'll always turn to face you while moving forward, and the result is that after a couple minutes, they'll all be right on top of each other. This is what you need, as your AE spell (Area Effect) only has a limited range - mobs need to be very close in order for you to damage them.<br><br>Run away a bit, as you need some space to cast lightning strike - it's got a rather long cast time. I usually run out of range and hit the cast button over and over again, so that when it goes off, I'm at max range.<br><br>That's all it takes. Of course, it's going to take several casts to take down all the specs, but when it's all said and done, you've taken down 4 mobs in the time it would take to kill one.<br><br>When you get good at this, and maybe a couple levels bigger, you can quad dervishes and cougars in iceclad. I would have 10-12 mobs running behind me while I was quadding - but AE spells can only hit 4 at a time. PBAE spells can hit as many are in range, but that's another, and more difficult topic.<br><br>Good Luck!</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8"></td><td align="right" id="fs8" >0 Replies</td></tr></table>
